== Sms

This Crabgrass mod allows users to opt-in to receive SMS notifications
when they receive a message, and respond directly via SMS.


== Usage

  Run SMS Migrations:
    $ ./script/generate plugin_migration
    $ rake db:migrate

  Add to config/crabgrass.ENVIRONMENT.yml:
    enabled_mods:
      - sms

  Run the unit tests:
    $ rake test:mods:all MOD=sms


  === Twilio

  If your users are based in the United States, I recommend that you use
  the Twilio backend. It's very quick and easy to get started.

  Create an account:
    https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio

  Install the twiliolib Gem:
    $ gem install twiliolib -s http://gemcutter.org

  Create config/sms.yml:
    development:
      backend:       twilio
      account_sid:   YOUR_ACCOUNT_SID
      auth_token:    YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN
      origin_number: YYY-YYY-YYYY


  === Clickatell

  Install the clickatell Gem:
    $ gem install clickatell

  Create config/sms.yml:
    development:
      backend:  clickatell
      api_key:  YOUR_API_KEY
      username: YOUR_USERNAME
      password: YOUR_PASSWORD
